To mark World Sight Day, the Envision Centre for Sight in Vanderbijlpark has given 100 patients the gift of sight. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Envision Centre for Sight in Vanderbijlpark has given 100 patients the gift of sight to mark World Sight Day. The centre performed free cataract surgeries from midnight on Wednesday through to Thursday. READ: SA violence's impact on mental health The patients will have their bandages removed on Friday and many have said they are looking forward to seeing their grandchildren for the first time, while others said they look forward to being able to drive again. World Sight Day is a global event, observed annually in October, and is meant to draw attention on blindness and vision impairment.